Japanese media reports indicate Japan's intention to nearly double its annual catch of Minke whales in the Antarctic, currently set at 440, and to hunt endangered humpback and fin whales.
Australia strongly opposes this move but refrains from boarding Japanese whaling ships to avoid accusations of piracy due to Antarctic Treaty obligations.
Prime Minister Howard and Attorney General Ruddock emphasize their opposition to Japan's whaling practices and vow to continue efforts for a South Pacific whale sanctuary.
Australia believes in non-lethal research methods and criticizes Japan's scientific whaling as disguised commercial whaling.
